As per {{AbstractCreatePageAction.doAdd()}}:
{code}
pageManager.saveContentEntity(getPage(), null);
contentPermissionManager.setContentPermissions(editPermissions, getPage(), ContentPermission.EDIT_PERMISSION);
contentPermissionManager.setContentPermissions(viewPermissions, getPage(), ContentPermission.VIEW_PERMISSION);

onAddComplete();
LabelUtil.syncState(getLabelsString(), getLabelManager(), getRemoteUser(), getPage(), true);
{code}

{{PageCreateEvent}} get's published *before* permissions are set and the labels sync'd... This is causing trouble in a plugin that tries to add permissions or labels upon creating of a page, because {{setContentPermissions}} and {{syncState}} would actually delete what was there :-(

Too late now to defer publishing {{PageCreateEvent}} 'cuz it'd cause other problems, but maybe creating another event? i.e. {{PageAddedEvent}}?

