With Confluence 2.7, we are introducing the 'System Administrator' and 'Confluence Administrator' permissions.

We are also retaining the legacy 'confluence-administrators' group (the super-user group).

To reduce the resulting confusion as much as possible, please add the following text to the Help tips on the 'Global Permissions' page in the Admin console:
{quote}
*Note:* The '*confluence-administrators*' group is independent of the 'System Administrator' and 'Confluence Administrator' permissions. Any user who is a member of the 'confluence-administrators' group has site-wide administration powers, regardless of any other setting. The settings on the Global Permissions screen do not affect the powers allowed to members of this group. 
{quote}

And add the following similar text to the 'Manage Groups' page in the Admin console:
{quote}
*Note:* The '*confluence-administrators*' group is independent of the 'System Administrator' and 'Confluence Administrator' permissions. Any user who is a member of the 'confluence-administrators' group has site-wide administration powers, regardless of any other setting. The settings on the Global Permissions screen do not affect the powers allowed to members of this group. *This group will be removed from a future version of Confluence*, so we recommend that you don't assign members to the group. [More about global permissions|http://confluence.atlassian.com/x/1R0C].
{quote}

