On the Userlister macro; Can, similar to the "content-by-label"macro an option be added to choose whether you want to show the e-mail and username of a user? Should look like this;

\{userlister:groups=name|e-mail=false|username=false}

Also I would like to be able to edit the name of the group 

\{userlister:groups=BLABLAEXAMPLE|title=EXAMPLE} 

The reason is that the userlister macro is useful, but sometimes showing too much information which is distracting.

To replicate:

1) Enable Userlistener from User Listener Plugin
2) Enter the wiki markup:
{code}
{userlister:groups=confluence-users|online=true}
and
{userlister:groups=confluence-users|online=false}
{code}

The first macro will display the inverse of what it's supposed to - it displays all the non-logged in users instead of all the logged in users.

The second macro will display all users, regardless of their login status.

Links in the body of some macros do not get changed when the page is renamed.  Worked correctly on *2.5.2* and is broken on *2.6.1*.  This is important because a site's links could be messed up after renaming and it would be a nightmare to try to find and repair all the damaged links.  The puzzling fact is that links get renamed properly inside some macros but not others.  I checked a few:
* Working:  panel, section/column, excerpt, color
* Not working:  table-plus (3.3.1), chart (1.8)

I looked through issues related to rename and did not notice any related changes between 2.5.2 and 2.6.1.  Was there some incompatibility introduced that requires a plugin change?

Simple example:
{noformat}
{table-plus}
[Rename this page]
{table-plus}
{noformat}

Related issue is [TBL-38|http://developer.atlassian.com/jira/browse/TBL-38]

